</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1986" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[263,642,151,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Umbilibalcis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis box="[263,358,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">crassula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[366,642,151,177]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dall, 1889 b)" baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[653,891,151,178]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Sticteulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[653,732,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">U. lata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dall, W. H." box="[748,883,151,178]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref33211" refString="Dall, W. H. (1889 b) Reports on the results of dredgings, under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, in the Gulf of Mexico (1877 - 78) and in the Caribbean Sea (1879 - 80), by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer ' Blake'. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 18, 1 - 492, pls. 10 - 40." type="journal article" year="1889">Dall, 1889b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jeffreys, 1883) (Bouchet &amp; Waren 1986)" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Umbilibalcis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subumbilicata">
<emphasis box="[947,1141,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">U. subumbilicata</emphasis>
(Jeffreys, 1883) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The present records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[603,800,187,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Umbilibalcis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[603,800,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Umbilibalcis lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents the first record of the the genus in the southwestern Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
The present genus resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[525,576,259,284]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Niso" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,576,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Niso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of microscopic sculpture of axial lines on the protoconch and teleoconch, but has a more rounded base and edge of the umbilicus, and lacks color on the teleoconch. Furthermore, the aperture of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[321,466,331,357]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Umbilibalcis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,466,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Umbilibalcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more rounded, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[767,818,331,356]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Niso" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[767,818,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Niso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is usually rhomboid.
</paragraph>
